🔷 Types of Middleware

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1️⃣ Application-Level Middleware

```javascript id="c2k8m4"
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log("App-level middleware");
  next();
});
```

---

2️⃣ Router-Level Middleware

```javascript id="d9m3v1"
const router = express.Router();

router.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log("Router middleware");
  next();
});
```

---

3️⃣ Built-in Middleware

```javascript id="e7k2r9"
app.use(express.json());
```

✔ Parses JSON

---

4️⃣ Third-Party Middleware

Examples:

* **morgan** → logging
* **cors** → cross-origin requests
* **helmet** → security

Install:

```bash id="f8n4s2"
npm install morgan cors helmet
```

---

5️⃣ Error-Handling Middleware

```javascript id="g3p7k8"
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  res.status(500).send(err.message);
});
```

📌 Must have 4 parameters

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 next() Function

`next()` is very important.

✔ Pass control to next middleware

---

### Without next()

```javascript id="h6r2m5"
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log("Stops here");
});
```

❌ Request gets stuck

---

With next()

```javascript id="i5k9p3"
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log("Continue");
  next();
});
```

✔ Works properly

---

🔷 Example: Logger Middleware

```javascript id="j4n8k1"
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log(req.method, req.url);
  next();
});
```

---

🔷 Example: Authentication Middleware

```javascript id="k9r2p6"
function auth(req, res, next) {
  if (req.headers.authorization) {
    next();
  } else {
    res.status(401).send("Unauthorized");
  }
}

app.use(auth);
```

---

🔷 Middleware Order Matters

```javascript id="l7m1p8"
app.use(middleware1);
app.use(middleware2);
```

📌 Executes in same order

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Route-Specific Middleware

```javascript id="m3k9p4"
app.get("/protected", auth, (req, res) => {
  res.send("Protected route");
});
```

